cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on image inpainting, which is a computer vision task, hence it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper proposes a deep generative model-based approach with a novel coherent semantic attention (CSA) layer, which involves training a neural network, making it likely to also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses the importance of modeling semantic relevance between hole features, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves experiments on datasets such as CelebA, Places2, and Paris StreetView, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR), making these sub-categories also likely.
